      • subtreeChanged

        public void subtreeChanged()
        Description copied from interface: PsiFile
        Called by the PSI framework when the contents of the file changes. If you override this method, you must call the base class implementation. While this method can be used to invalidate file-level caches, it is more much safe to invalidate them in PsiFile.clearCaches() since file contents can be reloaded completely (without any specific subtree change) without this method being called.
        Specified by:
        subtreeChanged in interface PsiFile
        Overrides:
        subtreeChanged in class PsiFileImpl
